text: Preheat the oven to 300 °F (149 °C).  Oil the sides and bottom of an 8 X 8 or 9 X 9 glass pan.  Get your ingredients all together. You will need to have set the eggs out for a few hours to get to room temperature.]] Add all of the ingredients into the bowl and mix thoroughly. You can do it by hand or with a mixing device. Use the spatula to spoon all of the batter into the baking pan after mixing together.  Bake in the 300 degree oven for 30 - 35 minutes.  Make sure that the brownies are done and then allow to cool for at least half an hour before removing from the cake pan.  Enjoy your brownies!  Finished.
